# Multiplayer 3D Builder

## Features
- Supabase Authentication (Email/Password + Google)
- Real-time shared 3D scene (React Three Fiber)
- Add/Move/Delete objects; live-sync via Supabase Realtime
- Player presence & labels
- Scene persistence (saved to Supabase)
- Responsive design (desktop & mobile)
- Deployed on Vercel

## Setup

1. Clone:
   git clone https://github.com/<you>/<repo>.git

2. Create Supabase project and run migrations (tables `objects`, `presence`)
   - Use the SQL snippets in `/supabase/migrations/*.sql`

3. Add environment variables:
   - `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-url`
   - `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key`
   - `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (only for server-side admin operations; do not expose in client)

4. Install:
   npm install

5. Run locally:
   npm run dev

6. Deployment:
   - Add env vars to Vercel project settings and deploy.

## How to run
- Sign up or sign in with Google.
- Create objects by clicking 'Add Cube' and clicking in the scene.
- Drag an object to move; click delete to remove.
- See other connected players in the player list.

## Notes
- Replace the Supabase keys in environment variables with your project's placeholders.
- Security: enable RLS and policies as shown in `/supabase/policies.sql`.
